longBusinessSummary: Endor AG develops and markets input devices for game consoles and PCs in Germany. The company provides high-end steering wheels and pedals for racing simulations on game consoles and PCs, as well as driving school simulators. It sells its products under the Fanatec brand primarily in Europe, the United States, Canada, Australia, and Japan through e-commerce. Endor AG was founded in 1997 and is based in Landshut, Germany.
